						               													<description>Criminal City, 2019.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Here, every day, the eternal struggle between the Law and the &amp;quot;Interstellar Mob&amp;quot; is rekindled without respite and shows no signs of dying out, also due to the scarce resources available to the police.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The 3 powerful interstellar criminal factions are fighting to command the entire city, fueling the black market, the corruption and the sense of insecurity of citizens, while few but brave space policemen face them every day to try to stop them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;And which side are you on?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Criminal City is a partially asymmetrical and semi-collaborative game for 3-6 players divided into a number of rounds depending on the number of players participating.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In each game a single player chose to be the head of a criminal faction(in this case he is playing as a &amp;quot;Interstellar Mob&amp;quot; Player) or, alternatively, can control policemen (1 or more, depending on the number of players).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The players who lead the criminal factions win individually by accumulating more Dominion Points (DP) than their rivals and trying not to be arrested by the space police. &amp;#10;The policemen win if they manage to capture all the factions fighting for the city's control within two consecutive turns or if, at the end of the game, they managed to limit the Criminals by accumulating at least 5 DP more than the most powerful faction.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
